# SKILL: Cloudflare Workers + D1 + R2 Architecture
*Portable skill for building Cloudflare Workers with D1 database and R2 object storage.*
*Tested on: clearsky-api Worker (873KB), oga-tools Pages project*

## Worker Structure
```javascript
export default {
  async fetch(request, env, ctx) {
    const url = new URL(request.url);
    const path = url.pathname;
    const method = request.method;

    // CORS headers (add to ALL responses)
    if (method === 'OPTIONS') return new Response(null, { headers: corsHeaders() });

    // Route matching
    if (path === '/health') return jsonResponse({ status: 'ok', version: 'v1-name' });
    if (path.startsWith('/api/...') && method === 'GET') { ... }

    return new Response('Not found', { status: 404 });
  },

  async scheduled(event, env, ctx) {
    // Cron handler — runs on schedule defined in wrangler.toml
    ctx.waitUntil(runScheduledTasks(env));
  },

  async queue(batch, env) {
    // Queue consumer — each message gets own CPU budget
    for (const msg of batch.messages) {
      await processQueueMessage(msg.body, env);
      msg.ack();
    }
  }
};
```

## Standard Helpers
```javascript
function jsonResponse(data, status = 200) {
  return new Response(JSON.stringify(data), {
    status,
    headers: { ...corsHeaders(), 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
  });
}

function corsHeaders() {
  return {
    'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',
    'Access-Control-Allow-Methods': 'GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS',
    'Access-Control-Allow-Headers': 'Content-Type, Authorization'
  };
}
```

## D1 Patterns
```javascript
// Single row query
const row = await env.DB.prepare('SELECT * FROM table WHERE id = ?').bind(id).first();

// Multiple rows
const { results } = await env.DB.prepare('SELECT * FROM table WHERE x = ?').bind(val).all();

// Upsert pattern (preferred over INSERT + UPDATE)
await env.DB.prepare(`
  INSERT INTO table (id, col1, col2, updated_at)
  VALUES (?, ?, ?, datetime('now'))
  ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET
    col1=excluded.col1, col2=excluded.col2, updated_at=excluded.updated_at
`).bind(id, col1, col2).run();

// Batch insert (max 1000 statements per batch)
const stmts = rows.map(r => env.DB.prepare('INSERT OR REPLACE INTO table VALUES (?,?)').bind(r.a, r.b));
await env.DB.batch(stmts);

// Pagination
const { results } = await env.DB.prepare(
  'SELECT * FROM table ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT ? OFFSET ?'
).bind(limit, offset).all();
```

## R2 Patterns
```javascript
// Write
await env.FILES.put(key, bytes, { httpMetadata: { contentType: 'application/json' } });

// Read
const obj = await env.FILES.get(key);
if (!obj) return null;
const text = await obj.text();
const json = JSON.parse(text);

// List with prefix
const listed = await env.FILES.list({ prefix: 'hubspot/threads/', limit: 1000 });
const keys = listed.objects.map(o => o.key);

// Delete
await env.FILES.delete(key);

// Check existence
const head = await env.FILES.head(key);
const exists = head !== null;
```

## wrangler.toml Patterns
```toml
name = "clearsky-api"
main = "worker.js"
compatibility_date = "2024-01-01"

# D1 Database
[[d1_databases]]
binding = "DB"
database_name = "clearsky-tools-db"
database_id = "YOUR_DB_ID"

# R2 Bucket
[[r2_buckets]]
binding = "FILES"
bucket_name = "clearsky-files"

# Cron triggers (multiple supported)
[triggers]
crons = ["0 2 * * *", "0 */4 * * *"]  # 2am daily + every 4 hours

# Queue producer
[[queues.producers]]
queue = "extraction-queue"
binding = "EXTRACTION_QUEUE"

# Queue consumer
[[queues.consumers]]
queue = "extraction-queue"
max_batch_size = 1
max_retries = 3
```

## Deploy Commands
```bash
# Deploy worker
cd C:\brand-presentations\infrastructure\clearsky-api
npx wrangler deploy

# Check health
curl https://api-tools.oga.earth/health

# D1 query directly
npx wrangler d1 execute clearsky-tools-db --command "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM hubspot_threads"

# Tail logs
npx wrangler tail --format=pretty

# Set secret
npx wrangler secret put SECRET_NAME
```

## CPU Limit Awareness
- Synchronous CPU limit: ~50ms per request
- AI calls (Claude, Mistral): must be async — use ctx.waitUntil() or Queue
- Large D1 queries: paginate, never load all rows at once
- Subrequest limit: 1000 per Worker invocation
- R2 reads within Worker: count as subrequests

## Gotchas
- NEVER create functions/ folder in Pages repo — breaks Cloudflare Pages deployment
- NEVER store large blobs in D1 (SQLITE_TOOBIG) — use R2 for anything >1MB
- Always add corsHeaders() to every response including errors
- D1 batch() limit: 1000 statements — paginate large inserts
- Secrets: never commit to git, use wrangler secret put
- Worker size limit: no hard cap but keep under 1MB for fast cold starts
- D1 JOINs with aliases: non-JOIN branch must NOT use aliases — D1/SQLite throws `no such column`
- Main fetch handler has no `method` variable — use `request.method` directly
- Exact string match routes MUST come BEFORE regex wildcard routes
- Worker propagation: 1-15 minutes. Preview URLs reflect new code immediately.
